    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The new smelter of the Panhan-\ndie Smelter company will begin\nwork May Is and will have a ca\npacity of $50 tons a dey. Frank\nw. Guilbert, secretary, and c. L.\nPugh, treasurer, will resign on May\nl, and George Heaton CT ST. Paul\nwill become secretary-treasurer and\nmanager. There will be no change\nmade in the Office of president,\nwhich is held by D. w. Cassidy. On\nMay 1 the company will move its\nmain Offices from Spokane to Sand\npoint, thought the heal office will\nnominally be maintained in Spo-\nkane."
